Jeanette Chabalala, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Two Gauteng students drowned during a team-building exercise at a conference venue in Pretoria on Saturday afternoon, paramedics said.&nbsp; Their boat capsized during an outing on a dam at the venue, Netcare 911 spokesperson Athlenda Mathe said.The two were part of a group of students attending a year-end function.The first student's body was recovered soon after the boat capsized. Paramedics performed CPR, but the student was declared dead on scene.A police search and rescue team helped recover the second body. Police were investigating. &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.